description:
&lt;p&gt;There are opportunities for Consultants in Anaesthesia with a special interest in Intensive Care Medicine to join an established, enthusiastic team mainly based at the Queen’s Hospital Burton (QHB). We will aim to accommodate specialist interest within Intensive Care and Anaesthesia.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;10PA jobs are available with 1.5 SPA. Additional sessions are available on request.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On call is currently TU only with a 1:6 frequency with ambitions to reduce this frequency to 1:8. The unit is well supported by middle grade &amp; trainee cover both in and out of hours.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates wishing to do anaesthetics lists at the Royal Derby Hospital will be accommodated following discussion with the clinical lead.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is a generous relocation package available to successful candidates. There is an option for mentorship for Consultants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All ICU consultants have office space on the unit and there is shared secretarial support available.&lt;/p&gt;
